1. Open the Execution Analyzer and Workbench windows.
  2. Build the script ClassLibrary, it can be found in the Execution Analyzer window under the Package with the same path as this package.
  3. Select the Analyzer script MyClassLibrary in the Execution Analyzer window.
  4. Create an instance of a class by selecting CRobert on this diagram and pressing Ctrl + Shift + J.
  5. The Workbench window will now have an instance of this Class.

This example demonstrates how Enterprise Architects Workbench can be used. The Workbench allows you to create ad-hoc instances of classes in the model. You can then examine the variable just as you would with a debugger and also invoke methods on the object.
